{"award_age":61.0,"bio_image":"full\/9315a46aa4baa47aa4a7c39592b5e991c407b80a.jpg","category":"Chemistry","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1953-06-24T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/d\/d6\/WE_Moerner.jpg\/220px-WE_Moerner.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/W._E._Moerner","mini_bio":"<p><b>William Esco Moerner<\/b> (born June 24, 1953) is an American <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physical_chemist\" title=\"Physical chemist\" class=\"mw-redirect\">physical chemist<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chemical_physicist\" title=\"Chemical physicist\" class=\"mw-redirect\">chemical physicist<\/a> with current work in the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biophysics\" title=\"Biophysics\">biophysics<\/a> and imaging of single molecules. He is credited with achieving the first optical detection and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Single-molecule_experiment\" title=\"Single-molecule experiment\">spectroscopy of a single molecule<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Condensed_phase\" title=\"Condensed phase\" class=\"mw-redirect\">condensed phases<\/a>, along with his postdoc, Lothar Kador.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/W._E._Moerner#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/W._E._Moerner#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Optical study of single molecules has subsequently become a widely used <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Single-molecule_experiment\" title=\"Single-molecule experiment\">single-molecule experiment<\/a> in chemistry, physics and biology.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/W._E._Moerner#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In 2014 he was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Chemistry\">Nobel Prize in Chemistry<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-nobelprize.org_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/W._E._Moerner#cite_note-nobelprize.org-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-sunobelwinner_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/W._E._Moerner#cite_note-sunobelwinner-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"William E. Moerner","place_of_birth":"Pleasanton, California","place_of_death":null,"text":"William E. Moerner , Chemistry, 2014","year":2014.0}